I realize that I am just an amateur at this, but come on people!<br>
<br>
Clerics - you get spell haste buffs.  So when my shaman asks for it, please don't shout at me various forms of &quot;You newb, clerics don't have haste!&quot;  I have independently verified this with a nice 65 cleric, so I know I'm not on crack.  You might even want to cast in on (gasp) all the casters in your group!<br>
<br>
Clerics - you can get aggro from your heals.  So maybe, when working in an adventure, you could either time your complete heals between fights or just not sit down right after you cast it.  Either of these would be preferable to yelling at tank01.  <br>
<br>
Rangers - you get a lovely spell called snare.  And for reference, the tornados in LDoN do run.  So snare them please.  If you're out of mana, stop nuking.  Snare is your job, learn it, love it, live it. Yes, I know its hard to get them snared sometimes.  No one is perfect.  <br>
<br>
Anyone not the main tank - New concept here!  Don't get riposted when the back of the mob is available!  Don't taunt for no reason!   <br>
<br>
Everyone - The time period between accepting an adventure is for finding the entrance, buffing, medding, getting roles straight.  Not for running to PoK to beg for KEI, Virtue, etc.  Not for training the rally point with Equestrielle or the pained unicorn.  Not for suddenly mentioning that you can't group with %%WORD196% or %%WORD197%.  <br>
<br>
%%WORD198% - It is not necessary to have a foolish message broadcast to say, group, raid, guild, tell, and shout every time you cast every spell.  Yes, announcing heals is a great idea.  Announcing debuffs is good too!  But do we have to hear &quot;Take that you puny %t eat hot flaming death&quot; every time you cast?  <br>
<br>
And last but not least - No, the shamans and clerics in your group cannot port you.  Well, we can, but we don't want to.  We're snobbish and don't like to port others.  So when you ignore my offer to cast Spirit of Wolf on everyone outside the dungeon before I self-port, don't whine and start running.  <br>
<br>
Ok, I lied.  My real last point is DON&quot;T PANIC.  The normal difficulty adventures aren't really that hard.  So if someone dies, goes linkdead, kei fails, we pull 3, or any other minor hiccup happens.... relax.   It will be ok.  I'll protect you.  <br>
<br>
